SVI seems to kills prompt adherance of Wan 2.2 I2V IMO, best when used with LORAs.  It also seems to make the slow motion problem worse.

widgets_values: A ginger domestic cat wearing a colorful knitted Viking-style hat with small horns and a rainbow yarn beard, its eyes wide and curious with a slightly goofy expression, walks slowly and confidently through a cozy, sunlit living room filled with soft fabric sofas, scattered books, and warm wooden furniture, the cats paws stepping lightly across the floor as its head gently bobs with each step and the yarn beard sways naturally, while the camera follows at a low-angle, medium focal length with a smooth follow-camera movement and subtle lens push, illuminated by warm daylight and soft side light streaming through nearby windows, creating low contrast and a homely atmosphere, presented in a cinematic, whimsical, heartwarming slice-of-life style with playful realism.

A ginger tabby cat with round green eyes sits upright in the center of the frame wearing a knitted Viking-style hat with small horns and a long rainbow-colored yarn beard, inside a cozy, slightly cluttered living room with soft furniture, books, and warm home decor blurred in the background, as the cat suddenly shakes its head left and right in a quick, playful motion causing the knitted horns and colorful yarn beard to swing and sway dynamically, while the camera performs a smooth surround camera orbit around the cat at medium close-up distance, maintaining facial focus, using a medium focal length lens, soft daylight from a window, gentle side light, low contrast, shallow depth of field, clean single shot, creating a humorous yet cinematic realism with natural fabric physics and a lighthearted, whimsical visual style.
A ginger tabby cat with wide green eyes, wearing a knitted Viking hat with small horns and a swinging rainbow yarn beard, sits in a cozy, softly lit living room with blurred books and furniture in the background, as the cat shakes its head and its body begins to morph smoothly and organically into a medium-sized golden dog, fur reshaping and facial features stretching in a seamless transformation, while the colorful yarn and hat dissolve naturally, and the newly formed dog immediately leaps forward to catch a flaming tennis ball flying through the air, the fire trailing sparks and heat distortion, with the dog snapping it confidently mid-jump, as the camera performs a continuous smooth orbit combined with a slight lens push-in, using a medium focal length lens, shallow depth of field, warm daylight side light, subtle motion blur, clean single shot, cinematic realism with magical transformation effects, dynamic fire VFX, and a whimsical fantasy-meets-live-action visual style.
